.TH STRNCPY 3 ""
.UC 4
.SH NAME
strncpy \- copy strings of limited length
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
.ft B
#include <string.h>

char *
strncpy(char *dst, const char *src, size_t len);
.ft R
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B Strncpy
writes exactly
.I len
characters into
.I dst
by copying string
.I src
to
.IR dst ,
appending '\e0' characters if
.I src
is less than
.I len
characters long, and
.I not
terminating
.I dst
if
.I src
is more than
.I len
characters long.
.B Strncpy
returns
.IR dst .
.SH EXAMPLES
The following sets ``chararray'' to ``abc\e0\e0\e0'':
.sp
.ti +0.5i
(void)strncpy(chararray, "abc", 6).
.PP
The following sets ``chararray'' to ``abcdef'':
.sp
.RS
(void)strncpy(chararray, "abcdefgh", 6);
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
bcopy(3), memccpy(3), memcpy(3), memmove(3), strcpy(3)
.SH STANDARDS
.B Strncpy
conforms to ANSI X3.159-1989 (``ANSI C'').
